1
00:01:40,690 --> 00:01:41,900
Where's Reiju?

2
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:45,910
Who knows? She went out earlier.

3
00:01:46,710 --> 00:01:48,790
♪ Tea! ♪

4
00:01:48,790 --> 00:01:50,840
♪ Tea! ♪

5
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:52,710
♪ Tea! ♪

6
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,830
♪ Green tea! ♪

7
00:01:49,830 --> 00:01:51,750
♪ Green tea! ♪

8
00:01:51,750 --> 00:01:52,750
♪ Green tea! ♪

9
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:55,380
♪ Which would you like to have? ♪

10
00:01:55,420 --> 00:02:00,890
Anyway, Father, where will Sanji
and his wife live after they get married?

11
00:02:00,890 --> 00:02:03,100
In Germa, of course.

12
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:10,020
If we don't hold her as a hostage,
we don't know what they'll demand hereafter.

13
00:02:10,020 --> 00:02:12,440
We're dealing with pirates.

14
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:15,810
I see. A hostage, huh?

15
00:02:16,780 --> 00:02:22,530
Maybe they'll want to hold Sanji hostage too,
in case something happens, y'know?

16
00:02:22,530 --> 00:02:24,680
Don't be stupid, Niji.

17
00:02:25,490 --> 00:02:31,500
Even if they do that,
would killing Sanji matter to us?

18
00:02:32,090 --> 00:02:33,520
You're right.

19
00:02:35,170 --> 00:02:36,670
It wouldn't!

20
00:02:36,670 --> 00:02:39,280
I can't wait...

21
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:42,440
to live with Sanji again.

22
00:02:55,850 --> 00:02:58,990
Please! Don't do it!

23
00:03:00,910 --> 00:03:03,950
I don't wanna be eaten!

24
00:03:07,090 --> 00:03:10,750
You guys are hungry, aren't you?

25
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:14,630
We're starving!

26
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:21,510
This will be the finest game dish ever.

27
00:03:22,260 --> 00:03:25,640
Don't... D-D-Don't eat me!

28
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:30,170
– Let me down!
– Just give up already.

29
00:03:40,140 --> 00:03:42,780
Brûlée has sealed her own downfall.

30
00:03:47,410 --> 00:03:48,830
What? What?!

31
00:03:57,910 --> 00:04:04,290
The Carrot that got caught
with me at that time was a fake.

32
00:04:04,290 --> 00:04:10,850
It's a frog that was transformed
into a mirror image of Carrot by Brûlée's ability.

33
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:15,310
The real Carrot...

34
00:04:18,510 --> 00:04:20,740
is in the attic.

35
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:24,570
Stop! Don't eat me!

36
00:04:24,570 --> 00:04:29,450
Please! Help! Chobro!

37
00:04:29,450 --> 00:04:32,040
Help me!

38
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:39,460
But... I feel bad for the frog.

39
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:44,660
There are 16 enemies in this house.

40
00:04:44,660 --> 00:04:49,620
The most troubling ones are
Randolph, Aristocroc,

41
00:04:49,620 --> 00:04:53,000
the mysterious chimney man Diesel,

42
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,700
and... Brûlée.

43
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:59,610
My only chance to catch them off guard...

44
00:04:59,610 --> 00:05:03,680
is the moment they drop the fake Carrot.

45
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:06,680
Randolph, cut the rope.

46
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,200
Okay.

47
00:05:11,020 --> 00:05:15,580
She's gonna freak out when she gets dropped in.
I'll put the lid on right away.

48
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,590
Here goes, Madame Brûlée!

49
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:25,340
Now! Carrot!

50
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:26,680
Uh-huh!

51
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:29,720
Winding up and...

52
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:47,030
What are you doing, Randolph?

53
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:52,120
Madame Brûlée,
someone came down from the attic!

54
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:55,590
What?!

55
00:05:55,590 --> 00:05:58,830
There are two rabbit girls!

56
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:05,960
Good!

57
00:06:06,810 --> 00:06:09,340
Calm down! Hey!

58
00:06:09,340 --> 00:06:11,430
Hurry up, Carrot!

59
00:06:11,430 --> 00:06:14,060
You can count on me, Chobro!

60
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:21,830
What is she gonna do?

61
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:24,910
Randolph! Just cut the rope!

62
00:06:24,910 --> 00:06:26,190
O-Okay!

63
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:35,740
Carrot!

64
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:41,580
Take this!

65
00:06:45,770 --> 00:06:48,760
What?!

66
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:51,930
Oh, no! You can't do that! No!

67
00:06:51,930 --> 00:06:54,240
Nooo!

68
00:06:55,850 --> 00:06:59,520
– Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!
– Madame Brûlée!

69
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:02,480
Ouch! Ow, ow, ow...

70
00:07:02,730 --> 00:07:05,660
Ouch! Ouch!

71
00:07:07,290 --> 00:07:09,200
All right!

72
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:15,220
Rumble!

73
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:18,430
– Madame Brûlée!
– This is bad news!

74
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,040
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow...

75
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,290
Oh, no!

76
00:07:23,290 --> 00:07:25,170
Madame Brûlée!

77
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:35,280
Electrical Luna!

78
00:08:22,270 --> 00:08:25,980
This is bad! I gotta tell Mama!

79
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:31,490
Leave it to me, Chobro!

80
00:08:31,850 --> 00:08:35,530
Choo-choo! Choo-choo!
Choo-choo and choo-choo and choo!

81
00:08:35,530 --> 00:08:41,290
Idiots! No one can catch up with me
once I start running...

82
00:08:42,160 --> 00:08:42,990
Ouch!

83
00:08:42,990 --> 00:08:44,290
Garchu!

84
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:45,750
What?!

85
00:08:46,510 --> 00:08:48,090
Guess who?

86
00:08:48,090 --> 00:08:49,950
What?!

87
00:08:49,990 --> 00:08:52,760
No, no, no... Let go of me!

88
00:08:52,790 --> 00:08:54,260
Not yet!

89
00:08:54,260 --> 00:08:56,840
I said "Let go of me"!

90
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,310
Okay.

91
00:08:59,060 --> 00:09:00,200
What?

92
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:03,060
I-I'm gonna crash!

93
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:05,560
I can't stop!

94
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:06,190
There!

95
00:09:08,830 --> 00:09:14,030
Yes! We beat Brûlée's group!

96
00:09:15,980 --> 00:09:17,990
Chobro!

97
00:09:17,990 --> 00:09:19,450
Alright!

98
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:24,700
Now we can use Brûlée's ability
to jump in and out of the mirrors!

99
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:29,080
Let's travel in this dimension
across the island to look for everyone!

100
00:09:32,220 --> 00:09:33,620
May I come in-nasu ?

101
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:34,710
Yeah.

102
00:09:35,420 --> 00:09:37,240
Thank you for going shopping.

103
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:39,640
No problem-nasu.

104
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:42,260
Um, I've got some news-nasu.

105
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:47,310
We're currently holding Straw Hat Luffy
and the Cat Burglar captive-nasu.

106
00:09:49,870 --> 00:09:52,140
They captured Luffy and Nami-san ?

107
00:10:02,220 --> 00:10:09,000
As long as you don't try to run away,
everything will work out just fine, Sanji.

108
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:15,590
And a male mink and Soul King
are still rampaging.

109
00:10:15,590 --> 00:10:16,880
Brook!

110
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:22,380
Sweet Commander Smoothie and Baron Tamago
went to subdue them-nasu,

111
00:10:22,380 --> 00:10:24,720
but they're still struggling to...

112
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:25,810
That's enough.

113
00:10:28,140 --> 00:10:29,940
Can I have my groceries?

114
00:10:29,940 --> 00:10:32,690
Yeah, here they are-nasu.

115
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:36,600
Note: "Nasu" = Eggplant.

116
00:10:32,690 --> 00:10:36,600
If you're hungry,
I can bring you something, like nasu.

117
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:38,070
No, thanks.

118
00:10:38,950 --> 00:10:41,840
Can I use this kitchen?

119
00:10:40,870 --> 00:10:41,840
What?

120
00:10:43,580 --> 00:10:49,090
Pudding-chan didn't show up for that last meal,
so I'll cook something for her.

121
00:10:49,090 --> 00:10:50,860
I see-nasu.

122
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:55,920
I'm worried about her.

123
00:10:55,920 --> 00:11:00,410
Yes, I heard that she
still doesn't feel well-nasu...

124
00:11:09,860 --> 00:11:11,350
These are the keys.

125
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:17,980
Pedro-san ! I'll do it!

126
00:11:17,980 --> 00:11:20,150
Damn you!

127
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:25,200
How dare you do that!

128
00:11:26,330 --> 00:11:28,410
I have to do it!

129
00:11:35,130 --> 00:11:37,890
Swallow Banderole!

130
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:52,270
I asked my partner to risk his life
before I came here!

131
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,110
I have to get what I need...

132
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:07,660
or I'll lose face!

133
00:12:15,170 --> 00:12:20,800
What do you mean, "I don't have a face to lose"?!

134
00:12:22,020 --> 00:12:24,050
Guards, can you hear me?

135
00:12:24,870 --> 00:12:26,210
Answer!

136
00:12:26,210 --> 00:12:27,690
I've got to hurry.

137
00:12:47,570 --> 00:12:50,910
Is the intruder in there?!

138
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:55,180
Mama! You didn't have to come!
I can handle this!

139
00:12:55,180 --> 00:12:57,670
Get out of my way, Smoothie!

140
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,690
Who are you?

141
00:13:14,690 --> 00:13:18,460
Don't you know whose treasure

142
00:13:18,460 --> 00:13:22,030
you're messing with?!

143
00:13:22,650 --> 00:13:24,320
Don't tell me it's...

144
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:30,740
Big Mom!

145
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:40,250
Oh? What a strange creature!

146
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:52,310
The intruder is passing
through the hallway near the courtyard!

147
00:13:52,310 --> 00:13:54,120
Corner him from both sides!

148
00:14:00,900 --> 00:14:03,670
All hands, shields up!

149
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:10,910
Charge!

150
00:14:18,450 --> 00:14:21,290
Almost there!

151
00:14:28,430 --> 00:14:31,780
Alright! We cornered him in the courtyard!

152
00:14:31,780 --> 00:14:34,830
Damn! What are they up to?

153
00:14:36,730 --> 00:14:39,210
It's been a while-bon !

154
00:14:46,780 --> 00:14:48,950
Baron Tamago!

155
00:14:48,950 --> 00:14:53,100
Captain Pedro of the Nox Pirates!

156
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:58,330
Although you're my enemy,
I've always respected you.

157
00:14:58,830 --> 00:15:02,340
And now that we're facing one another,

158
00:15:02,850 --> 00:15:06,960
the scars on our left eyes both twitch-toi-et-moi.

159
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:15,900
Five years ago, you really held on to your life.

160
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:19,180
Why have you returned?

161
00:15:19,180 --> 00:15:22,900
You don't have much time
left to live-soufflé.

162
00:15:24,970 --> 00:15:28,070
On that day, Mama took...

163
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:39,370
50 years of your life-bon !

164
00:15:42,790 --> 00:15:46,630
Yes, I know that.

165
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:55,320
I'm not...

166
00:16:00,750 --> 00:16:03,810
expecting to go home alive!

167
00:16:39,060 --> 00:16:41,080
Sanji!

168
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:44,560
Not here!

169
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,910
Sanji!

170
00:16:46,910 --> 00:16:49,150
Oh, there's a ghost!

171
00:16:51,820 --> 00:16:54,400
Not here, either.

172
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:03,220
Oh, my!

173
00:17:13,380 --> 00:17:15,690
Is it farther ahead?

174
00:17:15,690 --> 00:17:17,180
Wake up, Brûlée!

175
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:21,810
Where is the mirror that leads
to Whole Cake Chateau?

176
00:17:21,810 --> 00:17:24,480
Diesel! Do you know where to go?!

177
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:27,440
How would I know?! Dammit!

178
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:32,530
As long as we're touching Brûlée,
we can jump in and out of the mirrors!

179
00:17:33,990 --> 00:17:38,160
This dimension is connected to the mirrors
all across Whole Cake Island.

180
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:40,830
We should've reached the castle already.

181
00:17:40,830 --> 00:17:44,260
Brûlée! Wake up!

182
00:17:44,260 --> 00:17:45,410
C'mon!

183
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:49,640
Anyway, we gotta try to find it ourselves
until she wakes up!

184
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:52,740
Let's keep going until we find it!

185
00:17:54,370 --> 00:17:58,580
You guys will pay for this!

186
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:11,570
Stop it, Luffy! What are you doing?!

187
00:18:11,570 --> 00:18:13,690
It's no use...

188
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:21,760
If you don't stop,
you're going to rip off your hands!

189
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:23,770
That's what I'm trying to do!

190
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:24,950
What?!

191
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:27,480
No! Don't do it!

192
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:28,830
I have no choice!

193
00:18:28,830 --> 00:18:33,170
Is there any other way to get us out of here?!

194
00:18:33,170 --> 00:18:37,510
Isn't it better to have your arms torn apart...

195
00:18:37,510 --> 00:18:39,720
than to die?!

196
00:18:40,430 --> 00:18:42,950
A little more to go!

197
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:50,480
No, no, no!
They're getting thinner than before!

198
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,500
That's what I want!

199
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:55,940
While we're hoping for someone to come help,

200
00:18:55,940 --> 00:19:01,370
we'll lose everything,
and eventually get killed by Big Mom!

201
00:19:01,370 --> 00:19:07,080
That's so stupid!
I don't wanna die like that!

202
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:14,000
Tear yours apart, too!

203
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:16,800
What?! Are you crazy?! No way!

204
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:20,590
Then I'll take care of you too,
so quit moaning!

205
00:19:20,590 --> 00:19:23,460
I don't wanna see your arms
being torn apart! Stop!

206
00:19:23,460 --> 00:19:25,970
Don't be so unreasonable!

207
00:19:25,970 --> 00:19:27,810
I'm...

208
00:19:27,810 --> 00:19:31,250
not gonna die in a place like this!

209
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:33,560
No!

210
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:47,010
Crap. I made a ton, like I always do.

211
00:19:47,980 --> 00:19:51,570
I don't think Pudding-chan
will eat this much.

212
00:19:51,570 --> 00:19:53,670
What am I thinking?

213
00:19:56,570 --> 00:20:00,420
Oh, well, if she can't finish it,
I'll eat it.

214
00:20:02,590 --> 00:20:06,430
Whoa! You made a lot!

215
00:20:06,430 --> 00:20:08,470
But I can't eat this much.

216
00:20:09,060 --> 00:20:11,500
Why don't you have some, too?

217
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:13,200
Open your mouth.

218
00:20:15,020 --> 00:20:17,270
That'd be so nice!

219
00:20:20,850 --> 00:20:24,610
Pudding-chan, here I come.

220
00:20:26,070 --> 00:20:27,990
Are you going somewhere-nasu ?

221
00:20:28,870 --> 00:20:33,710
Yes, I'm going to get comforted
by my only ray of light in this world.

222
00:20:33,710 --> 00:20:37,460
Then do you want this eggplant-nasu ?

223
00:20:37,460 --> 00:20:39,170
Maybe later.

224
00:21:17,130 --> 00:21:21,840
Straw Hat and Cat Burglar are
already ours-bon.

225
00:21:21,840 --> 00:21:23,720
Give up-bon.

226
00:21:24,650 --> 00:21:27,040
So, what?

227
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:29,730
Then, let's have it out-bon !

228
00:21:58,140 --> 00:22:01,500
I'm not scared of the minks-bon !

229
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,240
I guess you're prepared.

230
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:07,800
That's right. I'm wearing special tights
that protect me from Electro-feuille.

231
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:11,800
I'm gonna sort things out with you here!

232
00:22:12,540 --> 00:22:14,810
Big Brothers! It's you guys!

233
00:22:14,810 --> 00:22:16,810
– What?! You...
– Pekoms.

234
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:19,270
Big Brother Pedro! Big Brother Zepo!

235
00:22:19,270 --> 00:22:20,500
Garchu!

236
00:22:20,500 --> 00:22:22,250
Garchu...

237
00:22:22,250 --> 00:22:23,670
Garchu!

238
00:22:23,670 --> 00:22:24,610
Garchu...

239
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,600
Why are you here?

240
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:31,310
I'm a member of the Big Mom Pirates now.

241
00:22:34,940 --> 00:22:37,460
– You'll lose more than an eye this time!
– You'll lose more than an eye this time!

242
00:23:09,490 --> 00:23:11,320
That was close-bon !

243
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:19,740
My left eye still twitches sometimes-feuille.

244
00:23:19,740 --> 00:23:23,460
I remember the pain of
getting stabbed by you-toilette !

245
00:23:23,890 --> 00:23:27,050
I remember too, of course.

246
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:31,840
Look what you've done, you thieves.

247
00:23:37,670 --> 00:23:39,680
W-What the...

248
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:41,140
Big Bro!

249
00:23:54,060 --> 00:23:57,410
I'm taking 100 years of your life!

250
00:23:59,940 --> 00:24:02,960
Stay with me, Zepo!

251
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:09,780
Zepo...

252
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:11,800
Zepo!

253
00:24:14,660 --> 00:24:16,510
Big Brother Zepo!

254
00:24:16,590 --> 00:24:21,390
There wasn't enough for 100 years.

255
00:24:21,390 --> 00:24:27,090
He only had 30 years to live.

256
00:24:28,360 --> 00:24:34,700
Since you're his partner,
I need you to pay the rest.

257
00:24:37,950 --> 00:24:43,460
Now, give me 70 years' worth of your soul!

258
00:24:43,460 --> 00:24:47,270
Please, Mama!
He's like a big brother to me!

259
00:24:47,270 --> 00:24:51,420
If you take 70 years,
Big Bro Pedro will die too!

260
00:24:51,420 --> 00:24:54,450
Stop, Pekoms. That's pathetic-bon.

261
00:24:54,450 --> 00:24:56,570
I'm begging you, Mama!

262
00:24:56,570 --> 00:24:57,680
Pekoms...

263
00:25:00,340 --> 00:25:04,600
Stop crying, Pekoms! All right.

264
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:08,770
10 years. I'll knock off 10 years.

265
00:25:08,770 --> 00:25:10,310
What?!

266
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:16,480
But you took away an eye from Tamago,
and that's serious.

267
00:25:17,450 --> 00:25:19,200
I'll take 60 years of your life!

268
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:30,000
Aren't you satisfied, Pekoms?

269
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:32,730
W-Well...

270
00:25:37,510 --> 00:25:40,100
Hey, Big Mom!

271
00:25:42,910 --> 00:25:45,310
How many years will you spare for this?

272
00:25:47,220 --> 00:25:49,900
Big Bro!

273
00:25:51,710 --> 00:25:56,700
It's pointless to die here!
The day of the new dawn is coming!

274
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:58,870
I must go back to my country!

275
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:09,220
You're so handsome.

276
00:26:09,220 --> 00:26:12,300
I'll reduce it to 50 years.

277
00:26:12,300 --> 00:26:14,840
Go on with your life.

278
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:21,200
Legs Benedict!

279
00:26:26,410 --> 00:26:32,070
Say it-bon, Pedro!
Why did you come back?!

280
00:26:34,710 --> 00:26:41,070
To this nightmarish island where your partner got killed
and 50 years of your life was taken away!

281
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:48,080
The Straw Hats saved my homeland,
and I'm indebted to them!

282
00:26:57,810 --> 00:27:04,680
On top of that, I believe they're the ones
who will lead the world to the new dawn!

283
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:13,150
Pedro!

284
00:27:13,150 --> 00:27:18,110
The new dawn is close!

285
00:27:24,730 --> 00:27:30,210
In time, the Straw Hats will surpass you people
and change the world!

286
00:27:31,420 --> 00:27:36,840
They can't do anything!
Where do you think you are-bon ?!

287
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:39,260
This is Whole Cake Island-bon !

288
00:27:39,260 --> 00:27:41,690
Does that matter?

289
00:27:41,690 --> 00:27:45,060
I believe in the Straw Hats.

290
00:27:45,060 --> 00:27:49,310
That's why I'm happy to spend
the short remainder of my life...

291
00:27:50,580 --> 00:27:53,400
helping them!

292
00:27:58,690 --> 00:28:01,200
But don't get me wrong.

293
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:03,740
I'm not gonna die here!

294
00:28:03,740 --> 00:28:07,290
They haven't fulfilled their reason
for being here yet!

295
00:28:25,030 --> 00:28:27,950
I'm not gonna die yet.

296
00:28:29,850 --> 00:28:32,770
Please. You let me through earlier.

297
00:28:32,770 --> 00:28:35,200
No means no, silly boy.

298
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:36,230
But why?

299
00:28:36,230 --> 00:28:42,240
Madam Pudding is currently busy:
B-U-S-Y.

300
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:43,860
"Busy"?

301
00:28:43,860 --> 00:28:48,120
I'll kick your butt, silly boy.
Go away, silly boy.

302
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:06,090
Wait a minute...

303
00:29:06,090 --> 00:29:09,970
I think there's a veranda outside her room.

304
00:29:29,620 --> 00:29:31,660
I can hand it in through the window.

305
00:29:34,870 --> 00:29:39,610
Maybe I shouldn't do this.
I'll look like a creep.

306
00:29:39,610 --> 00:29:43,950
Well... we'll be husband and wife tomorrow!

307
00:29:43,950 --> 00:29:46,340
So, even if she's changing...

308
00:29:46,340 --> 00:29:50,720
Or e-e-even if she's naked,
there's nothing wrong with it!

309
00:29:58,430 --> 00:30:01,900
Good. She's laughing.

310
00:30:03,780 --> 00:30:06,700
There she is. Pudding-chan !

311
00:30:08,450 --> 00:30:10,830
Who is she talking to?

312
00:30:12,790 --> 00:30:14,250
Reiju?!

313
00:30:14,250 --> 00:30:16,300
Why is she here?

314
00:30:16,300 --> 00:30:18,490
What does she want from Pudding-chan ?

315
00:30:28,310 --> 00:30:34,350
You must be dreaming!
Me, marry that lowlife?!

316
00:30:34,350 --> 00:30:36,800
Definitely not!

317
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:40,020
Definitely not!

318
00:30:46,180 --> 00:30:50,990
I'm Mama's favorite.
Especially when it comes to my acting skill.

319
00:30:50,990 --> 00:30:55,950
She cares about me so much,
that it can really get annoying sometimes.

320
00:30:57,160 --> 00:31:01,170
It isn't hard for me to keep her happy, since I can easily manipulate any man.

321
00:31:01,170 --> 00:31:04,220
Tricking the Straw Hats
was a piece of cake, too.

322
00:31:05,890 --> 00:31:11,090
Only my family knows my true nature.

323
00:31:21,060 --> 00:31:23,980
That little...!

324
00:31:23,980 --> 00:31:27,610
Man, he won't shut up.

325
00:31:27,610 --> 00:31:31,660
Damn... that Pudding!

326
00:31:31,660 --> 00:31:35,780
Luffy, stop!
They're really gonna be torn apart!

327
00:31:35,780 --> 00:31:38,500
I'll make her pay...

328
00:31:42,290 --> 00:31:45,700
no matter what!

329
00:31:47,820 --> 00:31:50,590
So, don't worry.

330
00:31:51,470 --> 00:31:54,760
I'm not going to marry him.

331
00:31:58,370 --> 00:31:59,520
Listen.

332
00:32:02,480 --> 00:32:05,540
I'm not going to marry him, because...

333
00:32:06,250 --> 00:32:10,610
he's an idiot that played right into my hands by falling for me...

334
00:32:13,530 --> 00:32:16,780
and because he's going to be shot in the middle of the ceremony...

335
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:21,120
by me.

336
00:32:24,080 --> 00:32:28,460
And you guys aren't going to survive, either.

337
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,600
Hey, wait, Pudding!

338
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:44,550
What are you talking about?!

339
00:32:48,770 --> 00:32:50,280
Goodbye.

340
00:32:50,280 --> 00:32:53,030
You pathetic rats.

341
00:32:54,610 --> 00:32:58,490
She was planning to set us up
from the beginning!

342
00:32:58,490 --> 00:33:02,660
What did Sanji ever do to her?!
Dammit!

343
00:33:04,870 --> 00:33:07,080
You people are so naive!

344
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:12,150
The evil army Germa 66?

345
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:16,050
Stay in your fantasy world,
you dumbasses!

346
00:33:23,380 --> 00:33:27,880
All Mama wanted was your army of clone soldiers...

347
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:30,790
and your advanced technology!

348
00:33:40,610 --> 00:33:42,920
You're so obnoxious.

349
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:45,290
My, aren't you defiant.

350
00:33:47,660 --> 00:33:51,690
That side of you means you won't obey us,
which is why we don't need you.

351
00:33:51,690 --> 00:33:56,820
The entirety of Germa is anchored
in our territory right now.

352
00:33:56,820 --> 00:33:58,740
You guys are nothing more than flies

353
00:33:58,740 --> 00:34:01,850
that took the bait of a sweet, irresistible, political marriage involving Sanji.

354
00:34:01,850 --> 00:34:03,530
Well done.

355
00:34:03,530 --> 00:34:06,480
It's gone just as Mama planned.

356
00:34:09,390 --> 00:34:11,320
At the wedding tomorrow,

357
00:34:13,680 --> 00:34:16,150
the entire Vinsmoke family...

358
00:34:20,810 --> 00:34:22,830
will be executed!

